HEADWORD: Restorationist
<hw>Res`to*ra"tion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who believes in a
temporary future punishment and a final restoration of all to the favor
and presence of God; a Universalist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Restorative</ent>⟦br⟧
